als, the concert hall, and film. Frontier Figures is a comprehensive illumination of what the West meant and still means to composers living and writing long after the close of the frontier.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aLegendszWest (U.S.)xHistory and criticism. 0aMusiczUnited Statesy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aaaron copland.  aamerican culture.  abook club books.  abooks about music composers.  abooks for music lovers.  abooks for reluctant readers.  acareer.  aculture and music.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aevolution of american music.  agifts for friends.  ahistory.  ahow to become a musician.  ahow was music created.  alearning about american music history.  amusic books.  amusic evolution.  apage turner.  aperforming arts.  apolitics in the music world.  athe wild west.  atheater.  avacation reads.  awhat was the wild west.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026778740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095202740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520952027423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520952027/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY